Hey Tess, nice video as usual, however: would you take a few minutes and inform yourself about how bad cruises are for the ocean, the environment in general (air) and local tourism?

It's actually way worse than flying (which isn't good either but still better than cruises, waste is getting dumped directly into the ocean and the amount of CO2-emissions is 3 times as high as on a plane. Local tourism suffers because people sleep on the ship and not in the hotels/apartments and sometimes don't even eat in the location they're visiting. Just a few thoughts (that you can confirm online easily). I don't mean to make you feel bad, but it's just something many people don't think about and maybe it could be avoided in the future. Otherwise I loved the video and you in general, so please don't take it personally. Cheers :)
